    "name": "microservices-dapr-aspire-workshop",
    "description": "# Microservices Dapr Aspire Workshop API\n\n## Overview\n\nThis collection provides a comprehensive set of endpoints for interacting with a **microservices-based pizza ordering system**. The system demonstrates modern cloud-native architecture patterns using Dapr (Distributed Application Runtime) and .NET Aspire for building resilient, scalable microservices.\n\n## Architecture\n\nThe pizza ordering system is composed of multiple independent microservices that work together to process pizza orders from creation to delivery:\n\n```\nCustomer → Workflow Service → Pizza Order Service\n                            ↓\n                    Pizza Storefront Service\n                            ↓\n                    Pizza Kitchen Service\n                            ↓\n                    Pizza Delivery Service\n```\n\n### Services\n\n| Service | Description | Base URL Variable |\n|---------|-------------|-------------------|\n| **Pizza Order Service** | Manages order lifecycle, storage, and retrieval | `{{pizzaOrderUrl}}` |\n| **Pizza Storefront Service** | Handles customer-facing order placement and validation | `{{pizzaStorefrontUrl}}` |\n| **Pizza Kitchen Service** | Processes pizza preparation and cooking | `{{pizzaKitchenUrl}}` |\n| **Pizza Delivery Service** | Manages delivery logistics and tracking | `{{pizzaDeliveryUrl}}` |\n| **Workflow Service** | Orchestrates the entire order workflow across services | `{{pizzaWorkflowUrl}}` |\n\n## Environment Variables\n\nBefore using this collection, configure the following environment variables with your service endpoints:\n\n- `pizzaOrderUrl` - Base URL for the Pizza Order Service\n- `pizzaStorefrontUrl` - Base URL for the Pizza Storefront Service\n- `pizzaKitchenUrl` - Base URL for the Pizza Kitchen Service\n- `pizzaDeliveryUrl` - Base URL for the Pizza Delivery Service\n- `pizzaWorkflowUrl` - Base URL for the Workflow Service\n\n**Example values:**\n```\npizzaOrderUrl: http://localhost:5001\npizzaStorefrontUrl: http://localhost:5002\npizzaKitchenUrl: http://localhost:5003\npizzaDeliveryUrl: http://localhost:5004\npizzaWorkflowUrl: http://localhost:5005\n```\n\n## Getting Started\n\n1. **Set up your environment**: Create a new environment in Postman and add all required variables listed above\n2. **Start with the workflow**: Use \"Start a new pizza order workflow\" to initiate a complete order process\n3. **Test individual services**: Use the direct endpoint requests to test each microservice independently\n4. **Monitor order status**: Use \"Get order status\" to track your order through the system\n5. **Validate orders**: Use the validation endpoints to approve or reject orders during the workflow\n\n## Workflow vs Direct Endpoints\n\n- **Workflow endpoints** orchestrate multiple services and handle the complete order lifecycle\n- **Direct endpoints** allow you to interact with individual microservices for testing and debugging\n\n## Common Use Cases\n\n- **Complete order flow**: Start workflow → Validate pizza → Check status\n- **Service testing**: Test individual microservices using direct endpoints\n- **Order management**: Create, retrieve, and delete orders\n- **Validation scenarios**: Test approval and rejection workflows",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
